      "id": "bug-008",
      "timestamp": "2026-05-28T13:10:30Z",
      "error_message": "WebSocket /ws/alerts rejected with HTTP 403 (websockets InvalidStatus) even though the route was added to main.py.",
      "file": "backend_api/main.py",
      "root_cause": "uvicorn --reload (WatchFiles) on Windows stalled: it logged 'Reloading...' but the new worker never started, so the old worker (without the new /ws route) kept serving. Starlette returns 403 for a WebSocket path that matches no registered route, which looked like a code bug but was stale code.",
      "fix": "Stopped the server and restarted WITHOUT --reload (run fresh on each code change). WS push then verified end-to-end: connect -> POST /ingest toxic -> alert pushed over the socket. Lesson: on Windows, prefer a manual restart over --reload for this project.",
      "tags": [
        "fastapi",
        "uvicorn",
        "reload",
        "watchfiles",
        "websocket",
        "windows",
        "403"
      ],
      "related_bugs": [],
